sub_title: Creating for Impact | SME | Renewable Energy | Frontier Markets | Private Equity | Accelerator | Tankelectrik | The Impact Investment Podcast
summary:
Willem Grimminck, is driven by passion for impact investment, company building and entrepreneurial ecosystems. He built One to Watch from the ground up starting in 2012, coincided by the investment in dairy. Doing so, Willem proved the potential that lies behind the challenging exterior of the Nepali economy and attracted additional investments from more than 30 private investors to Nepal. With a good sense of the needs of early-stage companies, Willem led the inception of ‘Rockstart Impact’ - the first business accelerator in Nepal. The accelerator has offered more than 1200 companies opportunities to scale and engaged a community of more than 100 mentors. Willem is an effective pioneer in frontier markets. He was instrumental in establishing the Nepal Private Equity Association with a view to improving the enabling environment for SMEs. Fueled by successes, Willem led the expansion of One to Watch in Myanmar. 

Crazy about endurance sports and playing the ukelele.
